    "details": {
      "description": "<p>A hyperrealistic vidgame pulls players into a virtual world, transforming them into pixelated avatars and pitting them against deadly challenges.</p>",
      "level": {
        "value": 4
      },
      "isComplex": true,
      "disable": "<p>@Check[computers|dc:22] (trained) to reprogram the game, or @Check[thievery|dc:22] (trained) to exploit a glitch, or @Check[Vidgame Lore|dc:17] (trained) to beat the game; four total successes are required to disable the trap</p>",
      "routine": "<p>(1 action) The trap presents the game's players with deadly challenges as 1 action. Each creature inside the game takes @Damage[(2d8+5)[slashing]] damage (@Check[reflex|dc:21|basic] save). A creature can attempt a Vidgame Lore check in place of their saving throw, if desired.</p>",
      "reset": "<p>The trap resets after 1 hour.</p>",
